Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for Memory Profiling Module

Tests all functionality of the advanced memory profiling, leak detection, and analysis system including:
- Real-time allocation/deallocation tracking with stack traces and metadata
- Advanced leak detection using reference counting and reachability analysis
- Memory fragmentation analysis with block mapping and visualization
- Thread-safe concurrent profiling for multi-threaded applications
- Export/import capabilities for external analysis tools and debugging
- Statistical analysis and trend detection for performance optimization
- Integration with allocators, GC, and runtime systems
- Performance-optimized profiling with configurable overhead limits (< 5%)
- Production-ready enterprise-grade memory debugging and analysis
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/memory/memory_profiling" as MemoryProfiling
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE be 1024
Let TEST_MAX_ALLOCATIONS be 100
Let TEST_STACK_TRACE_DEPTH be 10
Let TEST_LEAK_DETECTION_INTERVAL be 5
Let TEST_OVERHEAD_LIMIT be 5.0
Let TEST_FRAGMENTATION_THRESHOLD be 0.3

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus convert_to_string with value as error
        Return false

Process called "assert_equals" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is equal to expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_not_none" that takes value as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is not None:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message plus " - value is None"
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes value as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is true:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message plus " - expected true, got false"
        Return false

Process called "assert_false" that takes value as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is false:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message plus " - expected false, got true"
        Return false

Process called "assert_greater_than" that takes actual as Number and expected as Number and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is greater than expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected > " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_less_than" that takes actual as Number and expected as Number and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is less than expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected < " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_contains" that takes collection as List[Any] and item as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If collection contains item:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Collection does not contain: " plus convert_to_string with value as item
        Return false

Process called "create_test_profiling_config" returns MemoryProfiling.ProfilingConfig:
    Note: Creates a test profiling configuration
    Return MemoryProfiling.ProfilingConfig with:
        enabled as true
        stack_trace_depth as TEST_STACK_TRACE_DEPTH
        allocation_tracking as true
        leak_detection as true
        fragmentation_analysis as true
        performance_monitoring as true
        thread_safety as true
        export_enabled as true
        sampling_rate as 1.0
        max_allocations_tracked as TEST_MAX_ALLOCATIONS
        max_stack_frames as 50
        leak_detection_interval as TEST_LEAK_DETECTION_INTERVAL
        fragmentation_analysis_interval as 10
        overhead_limit_percent as TEST_OVERHEAD_LIMIT
        memory_limit_mb as 128
        metadata as dictionary containing
            "test_config" as true

Process called "create_test_pointer" that takes address as Integer and size as Integer returns MemoryProfiling.Pointer:
    Note: Creates a test pointer for allocation tracking
    Return MemoryProfiling.Pointer with:
        address as address
        size as size
        metadata as dictionary containing
            "test_pointer" as true
            "created_at" as Common.get_current_timestamp

Process called "create_test_allocation_info" that takes pointer_address as Integer and size as Integer returns MemoryProfiling.AllocationInfo:
    Note: Creates test allocation information
    Return MemoryProfiling.AllocationInfo with:
        pointer_address as pointer_address
        size as size
        timestamp as Common.get_current_timestamp
        stack_trace as list containing "test_function", "main", "entry_point"
        thread_id as "test_thread_1"
        allocation_id as "alloc_" plus convert_to_string with value as pointer_address
        allocation_type as "malloc"
        reference_count as 1
        tags as list containing "test", "allocation"
        metadata as dictionary containing
            "test_allocation" as true
            "allocation_source" as "unit_test"

Process called "simulate_allocation_activity" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiling.MemoryProfiler and allocation_count as Integer returns List[MemoryProfiling.Pointer]:
    Note: Simulates allocation activity for testing
    Let allocations be list containing
    
    For i from 0 to (allocation_count minus 1):
        Let address be 1000000 plus (i multiplied by TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE)
        Let size be TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE plus (i modulo 512)
        Let pointer be create_test_pointer with address as address and size as size
        
        MemoryProfiling.track_allocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as pointer and size as size
        Add pointer to allocations
    
    Return allocations

Process called "simulate_deallocation_activity" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiling.MemoryProfiler and pointers as List[MemoryProfiling.Pointer] returns Boolean:
    Note: Simulates deallocation activity for testing
    For each pointer in pointers:
        MemoryProfiling.track_deallocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as pointer
    Return true

Note: Core Profiler Creation and Configuration Tests

Process called "test_create_memory_profiler":
    Note: Tests creation of memory profiler with default configuration
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as profiler and message as "Profiler should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.config and message as "Profiler should have configuration"
    Let result3 be assert_true with value as profiler.config.enabled and message as "Profiler should be enabled by default"
    Let result4 be assert_true with value as profiler.config.allocation_tracking and message as "Allocation tracking should be enabled"
    Let result5 be assert_true with value as profiler.config.leak_detection and message as "Leak detection should be enabled"
    Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.allocations and message as "Allocations dictionary should be initialized"
    Let result7 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.stats and message as "Statistics should be initialized"
    Let result8 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.lock and message as "Thread safety lock should be initialized"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7 and result8

Process called "test_create_memory_profiler_with_config":
    Note: Tests creation of memory profiler with custom configuration
    Let config be create_test_profiling_config
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler_with_config with config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as profiler and message as "Profiler should be created with custom config"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.config.stack_trace_depth and expected as TEST_STACK_TRACE_DEPTH and message as "Stack trace depth should match config"
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.config.max_allocations_tracked and expected as TEST_MAX_ALLOCATIONS and message as "Max allocations should match config"
    Let result4 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.config.leak_detection_interval and expected as TEST_LEAK_DETECTION_INTERVAL and message as "Leak detection interval should match config"
    Let result5 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.config.overhead_limit_percent and expected as TEST_OVERHEAD_LIMIT and message as "Overhead limit should match config"
    Let result6 be assert_true with value as profiler.config.export_enabled and message as "Export should be enabled in test config"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_profiler_initial_state":
    Note: Tests initial state of newly created profiler
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as length of profiler.allocations and expected as 0 and message as "Should start with no allocations"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as length of profiler.deallocations and expected as 0 and message as "Should start with no deallocations"
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as length of profiler.leaked_allocations and expected as 0 and message as "Should start with no leaked allocations"
    Let result4 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.stats.allocation_count and expected as 0 and message as "Allocation count should start at zero"
    Let result5 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.stats.current_usage and expected as 0 and message as "Current usage should start at zero"
    Let result6 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.profiling_start_time and expected as 0 and message as "Start time should be set"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Note: Allocation Tracking Tests

Process called "test_track_single_allocation":
    Note: Tests tracking a single memory allocation
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    Let pointer be create_test_pointer with address as 1000000 and size as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE
    
    MemoryProfiling.track_allocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as pointer and size as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE
    
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as length of profiler.allocations and expected as 1 and message as "Should have one allocation tracked"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.allocation_count and expected as 0 and message as "Allocation count should be incremented"
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.stats.current_usage and expected as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE and message as "Current usage should match allocation size"
    Let result4 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.stats.total_allocated and expected as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE and message as "Total allocated should match allocation size"
    
    Note: Verify allocation is stored correctly
    If profiler.allocations contains pointer.address:
        Let stored_allocation be profiler.allocations[pointer.address]
        Let result5 be assert_equals with actual as stored_allocation.size and expected as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE and message as "Stored allocation size should match"
        Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as stored_allocation.stack_trace and message as "Stack trace should be captured"
        Let result7 be assert_not_none with value as stored_allocation.timestamp and message as "Timestamp should be recorded"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7
    
    Return false

Process called "test_track_multiple_allocations":
    Note: Tests tracking multiple memory allocations
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    Let allocation_count be 10
    Let allocations be simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as allocation_count
    
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as length of profiler.allocations and expected as allocation_count and message as "Should track all allocations"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.stats.allocation_count and expected as allocation_count and message as "Allocation count should match"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.current_usage and expected as (TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE multiplied by allocation_count) and message as "Current usage should account for all allocations"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.peak_usage and expected as 0 and message as "Peak usage should be tracked"
    Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.average_allocation_size and expected as 0.0 and message as "Average allocation size should be calculated"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Process called "test_track_deallocation":
    Note: Tests tracking memory deallocation
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    Let allocation_count be 5
    Let allocations be simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as allocation_count
    
    Note: Get initial state
    Let initial_usage be profiler.stats.current_usage
    Let initial_allocations be length of profiler.allocations
    
    Note: Deallocate first allocation
    Let first_pointer be allocations[0]
    MemoryProfiling.track_deallocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as first_pointer
    
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as length of profiler.allocations and expected as (initial_allocations minus 1) and message as "Allocation should be removed from tracking"
    Let result2 be assert_less_than with actual as profiler.stats.current_usage and expected as initial_usage and message as "Current usage should decrease"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.deallocation_count and expected as 0 and message as "Deallocation count should be incremented"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.total_deallocated and expected as 0 and message as "Total deallocated should be tracked"
    
    Note: Verify deallocation is recorded
    If profiler.deallocations contains first_pointer.address:
        Let stored_deallocation be profiler.deallocations[first_pointer.address]
        Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as stored_deallocation.timestamp and message as "Deallocation timestamp should be recorded"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_allocation_history_tracking":
    Note: Tests allocation history tracking for analysis
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    Let allocation_count be 3
    Let allocations be simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as allocation_count
    
    Let result1 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of profiler.allocation_history and expected as 0 and message as "Allocation history should be maintained"
    Let result2 be assert_less_than_or_equal with actual as length of profiler.allocation_history and expected as allocation_count and message as "History should not exceed actual allocations"
    
    Note: Verify history entries have required information
    If length of profiler.allocation_history is greater than 0:
        Let first_history_entry be profiler.allocation_history[0]
        Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as first_history_entry.timestamp and message as "History entry should have timestamp"
        Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as first_history_entry.stack_trace and message as "History entry should have stack trace"
        Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_history_entry.size and expected as 0 and message as "History entry should have size"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Leak Detection Tests

Process called "test_basic_leak_detection":
    Note: Tests basic memory leak detection functionality
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    Let allocation_count be 5
    Let allocations be simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as allocation_count
    
    Note: Simulate time passing for leak detection
    Let original_time be profiler.last_analysis_time
    Set profiler.last_analysis_time to original_time minus (TEST_LEAK_DETECTION_INTERVAL multiplied by 1000)
    
    Note: Run leak detection
    MemoryProfiling.detect_memory_leaks with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.leaked_allocations and message as "Leaked allocations should be analyzed"
    
    Note: Since we didn't deallocate anything, some allocations might be flagged as potential leaks
    Note: The exact behavior depends on the leak detection algorithm's sophistication
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.leak_count and expected as -1 and message as "Leak count should be tracked"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_leak_detection_with_references":
    Note: Tests leak detection with reference counting
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Note: Create allocation with references
    Let pointer be create_test_pointer with address as 2000000 and size as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE
    MemoryProfiling.track_allocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as pointer and size as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE
    
    Note: Simulate reference tracking
    MemoryProfiling.update_reference_count with profiler as profiler and pointer_address as pointer.address and delta as 1
    
    Note: Run leak detection
    MemoryProfiling.detect_memory_leaks with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.leaked_allocations and message as "Leak detection should analyze references"
    
    Note: Remove reference and test again
    MemoryProfiling.update_reference_count with profiler as profiler and pointer_address as pointer.address and delta as -1
    MemoryProfiling.detect_memory_leaks with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.leaked_allocations and message as "Leak detection should handle reference changes"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_leak_severity_analysis":
    Note: Tests leak severity analysis and categorization
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Note: Create allocations of different sizes
    Let small_pointer be create_test_pointer with address as 3000000 and size as 64
    Let medium_pointer be create_test_pointer with address as 3001000 and size as 4096
    Let large_pointer be create_test_pointer with address as 3002000 and size as 65536
    
    MemoryProfiling.track_allocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as small_pointer and size as 64
    MemoryProfiling.track_allocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as medium_pointer and size as 4096
    MemoryProfiling.track_allocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as large_pointer and size as 65536
    
    Note: Force leak detection
    Set profiler.last_analysis_time to profiler.last_analysis_time minus (TEST_LEAK_DETECTION_INTERVAL multiplied by 2000)
    MemoryProfiling.detect_memory_leaks with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.leaked_allocations and message as "Leak severity analysis should work"
    
    Note: Check if leak categorization is working
    If length of profiler.leaked_allocations is greater than 0:
        Let has_size_categories be false
        For each leak in profiler.leaked_allocations:
            If leak.leak_size_category is not None:
                Set has_size_categories to true
        
        Let result2 be assert_true with value as has_size_categories and message as "Leaks should be categorized by size"
        Return result1 and result2
    
    Return result1

Note: Fragmentation Analysis Tests

Process called "test_fragmentation_analysis":
    Note: Tests memory fragmentation analysis
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Note: Create allocations with gaps to simulate fragmentation
    Let allocations be list containing
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let address be 4000000 plus (i multiplied by TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE multiplied by 2)
        Let pointer be create_test_pointer with address as address and size as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE
        MemoryProfiling.track_allocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as pointer and size as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE
        Add pointer to allocations
    
    Note: Deallocate every other allocation to create fragmentation
    For i from 0 to 4:
        Let index be i multiplied by 2
        MemoryProfiling.track_deallocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as allocations[index]
    
    Note: Run fragmentation analysis
    MemoryProfiling.analyze_fragmentation with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.fragmentation_report and message as "Fragmentation report should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.fragmentation_report.total_blocks and expected as 0 and message as "Should detect memory blocks"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.fragmentation_report.free_blocks and expected as 0 and message as "Should detect free blocks"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.fragmentation_report.allocated_blocks and expected as 0 and message as "Should detect allocated blocks"
    Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.fragmentation_report.fragmentation_ratio and expected as 0.0 and message as "Should calculate fragmentation ratio"
    Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.fragmentation_report.recommendations and message as "Should provide optimization recommendations"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_fragmentation_scoring":
    Note: Tests fragmentation scoring and metrics
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Note: Create highly fragmented memory pattern
    Let allocations be list containing
    For i from 0 to 19:
        Let address be 5000000 plus (i multiplied by 1024)
        Let size be 256 plus (i modulo 3 multiplied by 128)
        Let pointer be create_test_pointer with address as address and size as size
        MemoryProfiling.track_allocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as pointer and size as size
        Add pointer to allocations
    
    Note: Create fragmentation by deallocating every third allocation
    For i from 0 to 6:
        Let index be i multiplied by 3
        If index is less than length of allocations:
            MemoryProfiling.track_deallocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as allocations[index]
    
    MemoryProfiling.analyze_fragmentation with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.fragmentation_report.fragmentation_ratio and expected as TEST_FRAGMENTATION_THRESHOLD and message as "Should detect significant fragmentation"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.fragmentation_report.external_fragmentation and expected as 0.0 and message as "Should calculate external fragmentation"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.fragmentation_report.average_block_size and expected as 0.0 and message as "Should calculate average block size"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of profiler.fragmentation_report.memory_map and expected as 0 and message as "Should generate memory map"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_fragmentation_recommendations":
    Note: Tests fragmentation optimization recommendations
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Note: Create fragmented allocation pattern
    simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as 15
    
    Note: Run fragmentation analysis
    MemoryProfiling.analyze_fragmentation with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.fragmentation_report.recommendations and message as "Recommendations should be provided"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of profiler.fragmentation_report.recommendations and expected as 0 and message as "Should have at least one recommendation"
    
    Note: Verify recommendations are actionable
    For each recommendation in profiler.fragmentation_report.recommendations:
        If recommendation is None or length of recommendation is equal to 0:
            Display message "  Empty recommendation found"
            Return false
    
    Let result3 be true
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Performance and Statistics Tests

Process called "test_memory_statistics_tracking":
    Note: Tests comprehensive memory statistics tracking
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    Let allocation_count be 20
    Let allocations be simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as allocation_count
    
    Note: Deallocate half of the allocations
    For i from 0 to 9:
        MemoryProfiling.track_deallocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as allocations[i]
    
    Note: Update statistics
    MemoryProfiling.update_statistics with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.stats.allocation_count and expected as allocation_count and message as "Allocation count should be tracked"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.stats.deallocation_count and expected as 10 and message as "Deallocation count should be tracked"
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.stats.active_allocations and expected as 10 and message as "Active allocations should be calculated"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.peak_usage and expected as profiler.stats.current_usage and message as "Peak usage should be higher than current"
    Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.total_allocated and expected as profiler.stats.total_deallocated and message as "Total allocated should be higher than total deallocated"
    Let result6 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.average_allocation_size and expected as 0.0 and message as "Average allocation size should be calculated"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_performance_overhead_monitoring":
    Note: Tests performance overhead monitoring
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Note: Perform operations and monitor overhead
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as 50
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    
    Note: Calculate and update overhead
    Let operation_time be end_time minus start_time
    MemoryProfiling.update_performance_counters with profiler as profiler and operation_time as operation_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_less_than with actual as profiler.stats.profiling_overhead_percent and expected as TEST_OVERHEAD_LIMIT and message as "Profiling overhead should be within limits"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.allocation_rate and expected as 0.0 and message as "Allocation rate should be calculated"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.performance_counters and message as "Performance counters should be maintained"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_memory_turnover_analysis":
    Note: Tests memory turnover rate analysis
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Note: Create allocation/deallocation pattern
    Let allocations be simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as 30
    simulate_deallocation_activity with profiler as profiler and pointers as allocations
    
    Note: Create new allocations
    simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as 20
    
    MemoryProfiling.update_statistics with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.memory_turnover_rate and expected as 0.0 and message as "Memory turnover rate should be calculated"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as profiler.stats.deallocation_rate and expected as 0.0 and message as "Deallocation rate should be calculated"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Thread Safety Tests

Process called "test_thread_safe_allocation_tracking":
    Note: Tests thread-safe allocation tracking
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Note: Simulate concurrent allocation from multiple threads
    Let thread1_allocations be list containing
    Let thread2_allocations be list containing
    
    Note: Thread 1 allocations
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let address be 6000000 plus (i multiplied by 1024)
        Let pointer be create_test_pointer with address as address and size as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE
        MemoryProfiling.track_allocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as pointer and size as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE
        Add pointer to thread1_allocations
    
    Note: Thread 2 allocations
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let address be 7000000 plus (i multiplied by 1024)
        Let pointer be create_test_pointer with address as address and size as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE
        MemoryProfiling.track_allocation with profiler as profiler and pointer as pointer and size as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE
        Add pointer to thread2_allocations
    
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as length of profiler.allocations and expected as 20 and message as "All allocations should be tracked safely"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as profiler.stats.allocation_count and expected as 20 and message as "Allocation count should be correct with concurrent access"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_thread_local_profiling_data":
    Note: Tests thread-local profiling data management
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Note: Set thread-local data
    MemoryProfiling.set_thread_local_data with profiler as profiler and thread_id as "test_thread_1" and key as "allocator_type" and value as "pool"
    MemoryProfiling.set_thread_local_data with profiler as profiler and thread_id as "test_thread_2" and key as "allocator_type" and value as "stack"
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as profiler.thread_local_data and message as "Thread-local data should be maintained"
    
    Note: Get thread-local data
    Let thread1_data be MemoryProfiling.get_thread_local_data with profiler as profiler and thread_id as "test_thread_1" and key as "allocator_type"
    Let thread2_data be MemoryProfiling.get_thread_local_data with profiler as profiler and thread_id as "test_thread_2" and key as "allocator_type"
    
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as thread1_data and expected as "pool" and message as "Thread 1 data should be correct"
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as thread2_data and expected as "stack" and message as "Thread 2 data should be correct"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Export and Import Tests

Process called "test_profiling_data_export":
    Note: Tests export of profiling data for analysis
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as 15
    
    Note: Export profiling data
    Let export_data be MemoryProfiling.export_profiling_data with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as export_data and message as "Export data should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as export_data["statistics"] and message as "Export should include statistics"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as export_data["allocations"] and message as "Export should include allocations"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as export_data["fragmentation_report"] and message as "Export should include fragmentation report"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as export_data["metadata"] and message as "Export should include metadata"
    Let result6 be assert_greater_than with actual as export_data["statistics"]["allocation_count"] and expected as 0 and message as "Export should contain valid statistics"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_profiling_data_import":
    Note: Tests import of profiling data
    Let source_profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as source_profiler and allocation_count as 10
    
    Let export_data be MemoryProfiling.export_profiling_data with profiler as source_profiler
    
    Note: Create new profiler and import data
    Let target_profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    MemoryProfiling.import_profiling_data with profiler as target_profiler and data as export_data
    
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as target_profiler.stats.allocation_count and expected as source_profiler.stats.allocation_count and message as "Allocation count should be imported"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as length of target_profiler.allocations and expected as length of source_profiler.allocations and message as "Allocations should be imported"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_json_export_format":
    Note: Tests JSON export format for external tools
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as 5
    
    Let json_export be MemoryProfiling.export_to_json with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as json_export and message as "JSON export should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of json_export and expected as 50 and message as "JSON export should have substantial content"
    
    Note: Verify JSON can be parsed back
    Let parsed_data be MemoryProfiling.parse_json_export with json_string as json_export
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as parsed_data and message as "JSON export should be parseable"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: AI/Agent Integration Tests

Process called "test_ai_profiling_analysis_api":
    Note: Tests AI-friendly profiling analysis APIs
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as 25
    
    Note: Generate AI-friendly analysis report
    Let ai_analysis be MemoryProfiling.generate_ai_analysis with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as ai_analysis and message as "AI analysis should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as ai_analysis["memory_health"] and message as "AI analysis should include memory health"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as ai_analysis["leak_risk_assessment"] and message as "AI analysis should include leak risk"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as ai_analysis["optimization_opportunities"] and message as "AI analysis should include optimization opportunities"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as ai_analysis["performance_metrics"] and message as "AI analysis should include performance metrics"
    Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as ai_analysis["recommendations"] and message as "AI analysis should include recommendations"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_agent_memory_monitoring":
    Note: Tests agent-driven memory monitoring
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler
    
    Note: Set up agent monitoring configuration
    Let monitoring_config be dictionary containing
        "agent_id" as "memory_monitor_agent"
        "monitoring_interval" as 1000
        "alert_thresholds" as dictionary containing
            "memory_usage_mb" as 100
            "leak_count" as 5
            "fragmentation_ratio" as 0.4
        "actions" as list containing "alert", "optimize", "report"
    
    MemoryProfiling.configure_agent_monitoring with profiler as profiler and config as monitoring_config
    
    Note: Simulate memory activity
    simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as 30
    
    Note: Trigger agent monitoring
    Let monitoring_report be MemoryProfiling.run_agent_monitoring with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as monitoring_report and message as "Agent monitoring should generate report"
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as monitoring_report["agent_id"] and message as "Report should include agent ID"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as monitoring_report["status"] and message as "Report should include status"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as monitoring_report["alerts"] and message as "Report should include alerts"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as monitoring_report["recommendations"] and message as "Report should include recommendations"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Note: Production Readiness Tests

Process called "test_enterprise_profiling_features":
    Note: Tests enterprise-grade profiling features
    Let config be create_test_profiling_config
    Set config.memory_limit_mb to 512
    Set config.overhead_limit_percent to 2.0
    
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler_with_config with config as config
    
    Note: Generate enterprise profiling report
    simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as 100
    MemoryProfiling.analyze_fragmentation with profiler as profiler
    MemoryProfiling.detect_memory_leaks with profiler as profiler
    
    Let enterprise_report be MemoryProfiling.generate_enterprise_report with profiler as profiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report and message as "Enterprise report should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report["executive_summary"] and message as "Report should include executive summary"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report["detailed_analysis"] and message as "Report should include detailed analysis"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report["performance_impact"] and message as "Report should include performance impact"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report["compliance_metrics"] and message as "Report should include compliance metrics"
    Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as enterprise_report["action_items"] and message as "Report should include action items"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_production_safety_limits":
    Note: Tests production safety limits and guardrails
    Let config be create_test_profiling_config
    Set config.overhead_limit_percent to 1.0
    Set config.max_allocations_tracked to 10
    
    Let profiler be MemoryProfiling.create_memory_profiler_with_config with config as config
    
    Note: Attempt to exceed limits
    simulate_allocation_activity with profiler as profiler and allocation_count as 20
    
    Note: Profiler should enforce limits
    Let result1 be assert_less_than_or_equal with actual as length of profiler.allocations and expected as config.max_allocations_tracked and message as "Should enforce allocation tracking limit"
    Let result2 be assert_less_than with actual as profiler.stats.profiling_overhead_percent and expected as (config.overhead_limit_percent multiplied by 2) and message as "Should monitor overhead limits"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Helper Functions for Complex Tests

Process called "assert_less_than_or_equal" that takes actual as Number and expected as Number and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is less than or equal to expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected <= " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "convert_to_string" that takes value as Any returns String:
    Note: Converts any value to string representation
    Return "test_value"

Note: Main Test Execution

